               <sense xml:id="Dmain" xml:lang="la" source="#dillmann"> <gramGrp> <pos expand="Substantivum">subst.</pos> </gramGrp>, dubiae significationis: <cit type="translation" xml:lang="la"><quote> uter aquarius </quote></cit> vel <cit type="translation" xml:lang="la"><quote> guttus </quote></cit>? an <cit type="translation" xml:lang="la"><quote> humidi </quote></cit> quid vel <cit type="translation" xml:lang="la"><quote> liquidi </quote></cit>?: (Pantaleon) <foreign xml:lang="gez">እምብዙኅ፡ ንዋይ፡ ጽድቀ፡ ዘአፍቀርከ። ሐወ፡ ዘዐቈርከ፡ በመርወይ፡</foreign> Deg. </sense>
               
            <sense xml:id="Tmain" xml:lang="en" source="#traces"> <cit type="transcription" xml:lang="gez"><quote> marway </quote></cit> <lb/>
 <foreign xml:lang="gez">አተዉ፡ ሰብአነ፡ ወወሀቦሙ፡ ንጉሥ፡ ብዙኅ፡ ንዋየ፡ ፵፡ አብቅለ፡ ወ፵፡ አልባሰ፡ መርወይ።</foreign> <cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><quote> ʻOur men have returned and the king has given them plenty of goods: forty mules, forty märwäy garmentsʼ </quote></cit> <bibl><ptr target="bm:Tedros2015Yonas"/><citedRange unit="page"> 64 (360) l. 11–12 (ed.); 65 (361) l. 14–15 (tr.)</citedRange></bibl> (‘I could not figure out the meaning of this term, whose root is plausibly <cit type="transcription" xml:lang="gez"><quote> räwäyä </quote></cit> {<lbl expand="videas">vid.</lbl> <foreign xml:lang="gez">ረወየ፡</foreign>} “to be satisfied”.The term recurs in some other hagiographic works, cf. <bibl><ptr target="bm:Bausi2003Libanos"/><citedRange unit="page"> 174</citedRange></bibl>, <bibl><ptr target="bm:Bausi2003LibanosTr"/><citedRange unit="page"> 48</citedRange></bibl>.’ <bibl><ptr target="bm:Tedros2015Yonas"/><citedRange unit="page"> 65 (361) n. 98</citedRange></bibl>) <sense n="L" xml:id="TL"> <foreign xml:lang="gez">መርወይ</foreign> <cit type="transcription" xml:lang="gez"><quote>marway</quote></cit> (<bibl><ptr target="bm:AlaqaTayya1965MSawasew"/></bibl>, <bibl><ptr target="bm:KidaneWaldGeezGramDict"/></bibl>) <cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><quote>leather bottle</quote></cit>, <cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><quote>canteen</quote></cit>, <cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><quote>tumbler</quote></cit> <bibl><ptr target="bm:Leslau1987dic"/><citedRange unit="page"> 478a</citedRange></bibl> 
</sense> </sense>
